headline: Lithium stocks tumble after report of CATL mine resuming production
summary: Investing.com -- Lithium producers faced significant pressure Tuesday as Albemarle (NYSE:ALB) stock fell 12%, Lithium Americas (NYSE:LAC) dropped 4.5%, and SQM (NYSE:SQM) declined 6% following reports that a major Chinese lithium mine will soon resume operations.
